<HEADLINE>
<P>
IMPORT PROTEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I wish to register an objection to the San Diego city plan to accept a 
$12-million bid for telephone equipment from a Japanese company. 
</P>
<P>
Why should taxpayers contribute to the U.S. trade deficit with Japan just to 
save a few dollars? 
</P>
<P>
On another page of The Times, an article stated that Japan and other Pacific 
Rim countries are being charged with "dumping" telephone products in this 
country by the U.S. government. 
</P>
<P>
SHIRLEY SCOTT 
</P>
<P>
Vista 
</P>
</TEXT>
