<P>
DOMINGUEZ HILLS GETS FEDERAL NURSING GRANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Statewide Nursing Program, based at California State University, Dominguez 
Hills, has been awarded a $163,000 grant from the federal Department of Health 
and Human Services to provide stipends for nurses pursuing graduate studies in 
nursing. 
</P>
<P>
Grants are awarded based on the number of students in a program and the quality 
and success of that program. More than 3,000 nurses are completing degrees 
through the Statewide Nursing Program, which is taught through hospitals and 
community colleges statewide. For more information about the program, call 
(800) 344-5484. 
