<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEUSCHATZ MEMORIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am an infrequent reader of the Real Estate Section of the L.A. Times since I 
cannot imagine being able to afford "upgrading" from my condo in Studio City. 
</P>
<P>
However, for some reason I opened that section this morning to find Sam Hall 
Kaplan's wonderful column on my dear friend Royce Schaffer Neuschatz (July 23). 
</P>
<P>
I, too, was at the memorial for Royce and when I went hiking yesterday in 
Griffith Park with the Sierra Club, I saw the old zoo picnic area and 
immediately thought of her. I began telling my "hike mate" of this terrific 
woman. 
</P>
<P>
Kaplan's idea is most fitting for Royce and I think she would heartily endorse 
it. As Kaplan requested, I will contact the commission directly with my 
support. 
</P>
<P>
SHARON MAYER 
</P>
<P>
Studio City 
</P>
