<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: TITLE FIRMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LINDA MARTINI-POSNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Harolyn Crandall has been named vice president of commercial/industrial sales 
at North American Title Co., Beverly Hills. The firm is a subsidiary of 
Glendale Federal Bank and serves California developers, realtors, financial 
institutions and the single-family marketplace. 
</P>
<P>
Law Firms 
</P>
<P>
Jay M. Davis has been elected president of the Los Angeles Headquarters City 
Assn. for 1989-90. Davis is partner in Baker McKenzie and is based at the 
firm's Los Angeles office. 
</P>
<P>
Consultants 
</P>
<P>
Sanford Goodkin, executive director of real estate consulting for Peat Marwick 
Main &amp; Co., will be redirecting his energies into the Los Angeles 
marketplace. The Goodkin Group joined Peat Marwick in 1987 and Goodkin has 
continued to service clients on master-planned communities and commercial 
development projects. 
</P>
<P>
Laventhol &amp; Horwath has appointed G. Allan Daum director of real estate 
services of its Costa Mesa office. Daum will focus on expanding the practice, 
with particular emphasis on corporations, developers and institutional 
investors. 
</P>
<P>
Jack D. Crevier, president of J. D. Crevier &amp; Associates Inc. in Van Nuys, 
has been elected president of the Consulting Engineers Assn. of California for 
a one-year term. 
</P>
<P>
Christopher J. Clifford is a new addition to Langdon Rieder Corp. As senior 
vice president of corporate accounts of the Los Angeles-based company, Clifford 
will concentrate on the downtown area, assuming responsibility for existing and 
new corporate clients. 
</P>
<P>
Toshihisa Ishiwata has joined the investment and consulting firm FLIC Inc. as 
manager of its Los Angeles office. Ishiwata will direct new business 
development with Japanese clients and serve as a liaison to the Tokyo office. 
</P>
<P>
Brokers 
</P>
<P>
Keith Keppler has become president of the Los Angeles-based Faulkner Co. His 
responsibilities will include overseeing the company's national and 
international expansion program. Keppler came on board in 1988 and directed the 
firm's relocation management resources division. 
</P>
<P>
The Santa Ana office of Coldwell Banker Commercial Real Estate Services has 
announced the appointment of Patrick Kendall to vice president and resident 
manager. 
</P>
<P>
Richard Fields has joined Tri Pacific Commercial Brokerage Inc. of Irvine as 
retail leasing specialist. 
</P>
<P>
Debra Z. Melikian has been named vice president of operations at Sperry Van 
Ness, a Newport Beach-based firm specialized in shopping centers, apartments, 
land, office buildings and industrial parks. Her duties will include 
coordinating special events, marketing and business development. 
</P>
<P>
Prudential Real Estate Affiliates Inc., headquartered in Costa Mesa, has named 
Patrick Scott vice president and regional director. Scott will be in charge of 
administration activities covering an 11-state area. 
</P>
<P>
Bruce A. Frasco has been named Beitler Commercial Realty Services' vice 
president and manager for the Sherman Oaks and Woodland Hills offices. He will 
coordinate the company's expansion effort and develop a strategy to centralize 
operations. 
</P>
<P>
Gasper Guarrasi has been appointed to the newly created position of vice 
president of finance and administration of the Landmark Realty Group of 
companies. Guarrasi will be the chief financial officer. 
</P>
<P>
Fred Sands Estates has announced the acquisition of Ron Abrams Realtors and the 
affiliation of Ron Abrams, who will assume the title of director of business 
development and will be headquartered at the Beverly Hills office. 
</P>
<P>
Richard A. Muller has been named branch manager of the 85-year-old firm of Daum 
Commercial Industrial Estate. He will manage its Carlsbad office. 
</P>
<P>
ACCOLADES: Joseph P. Brown, founder of Brown Realtors, has received an honorary 
doctorate of law degree from California Lutheran University in recognition of 
his continuous support of CLU and his 30 years of quality service to Ventura 
County. 
</P>
<P>
Developers/Builders 
</P>
<P>
Reginald J. Jackson has been promoted from project manager to vice 
president/project executive of Morley Construction Co., Los Angeles. He joined 
the 42-year-old construction firm in 1985. An architectural engineer, with a 
degree from the University of Illinois, he was at Jones Brothers Construction 
before joining Morley. 
</P>
<P>
The Orange County Region of the Building Industry Assn. of Southern California 
has announced Thomas F. Daly as its new director of governmental affairs. He 
was executive assistant to Orange County Supervisor Don Roth. 
</P>
<P>
Daniel P. Gerken has joined Newport Beach-based J. M. Peters Co. as director of 
forward planning. Gerken will be in charge of governmental processing and 
improvement planning for the company's projects in Orange and Los Angeles 
counties. 
</P>
<P>
Lenders 
</P>
<P>
Karinn Bostwick has been promoted to vice president, Real Estate Industries 
Group, Wells Fargo Bank. She is assigned to the Newport Beach office where she 
will be in charge of commercial, industrial and residential construction loans 
in the Southland. LINDA MARTINI-POSNER 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Christopher J. Clifford; Photo, Keith Keppler; Photo, Debra Z. Melikian; 
Photo, Gasper Guarrasi; Photo, Ron Abrams; Photo, Reginald J. Jackson 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
