<SECTION>
<P>
Part 1; Page 2; Column 6; Metro Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
69 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A burglar dubbed "The Weasel" has been pilfering canned food, flashlights and 
toilet paper from cabins in the Diablo Range that borders Stanislaus and Santa 
Clara counties. "It sounds like a . . . person up there is stealing what he 
needs to survive," Stanislaus County Sheriff's Capt. Les Weidman said. The 
burglar, who's been seen several times, has broken into more than 30 cabins 
over the last four months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
BURGLARIES -- CALIFORNIA 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
