</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two Palestinian prisoners at a desert detention camp were stabbed to death by 
other political detainees, the Israeli army said. It was not clear if the 
slayings were politically motivated. An army spokesman said the bodies were 
discovered during a count of prisoners at the Ketziot Detention Center. "They 
were killed by fellow inmates," an army spokesman said. Palestinian inmates 
have killed several other detainees accused of collaborating with Israeli 
authorities in the Negev Desert camp, which holds Palestinians in connection 
with the uprising against Israeli control of the occupied territories. 
</P>
