<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
African nations are determined to ban England from next winter's Commonwealth 
Games as punishment for allowing its athletes to tour South Africa, said 
anti-apartheid leader Sam Ramsamy. 
</P>
<P>
"The African nations feel the culprit countries ought to be excluded," Ramsamy 
said. "As always, England is acting arrogantly." 
</P>
<P>
Anti-apartheid officials condemned an English cricket tour of South Africa and 
warned rugby players against a similar visit. 
</P>
