<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rookie Steve Walsh completed all six of his passes to lead the Dallas Cowboys 
to a 14-3 victory over the San Diego Chargers in a scrimmage at Thousand Oaks. 
Troy Aikman, the first player selected in the NFL draft, completed three of 
five passes for 26 yards. 
</P>
<P>
Coach Jimmy Johnson said he won't name a starting quarterback until the final 
exhibition game against Houston on Sept. 2. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson and Cowboy owner Jerry Jones also said they have been so impressed with 
their training camp at Cal Lutheran University that they likely will come back 
next year. Earlier, they said the Cowboys would probably hold training camp in 
Texas next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
