<TEXT>
<P>
Bill Shoemaker, the winningest jockey in history, rode Drone's Dash from 25 
lengths behind to win in his final race at Philadelphia Park in Cornwell 
Heights, Pa. 
</P>
<P>
Shoemaker, 57, who has 8,803 wins, also came in second twice and fourth once at 
the Bucks County track in Bensalem Township. 
</P>
<P>
Saturday's races were part of Shoemaker's farewell tour, scheduled to end Feb. 
4 at Santa Anita. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
